The paper deals with the problem of video object segmentation, which is a topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves the use of multiple hypotheses and a gating scheme, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the development of a novel mask propagation score, which is a metric used to evaluate the quality of the segmentation, and this is a topic in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the use of motion models and tracking, which are topics in multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO).
